latestIgtvVideos.title: GRWM for Diwai! ✨
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Happy Chohti Diwali everyone! 
I hope you are all safe and with your families having the most amazing time. 

Now 2020 hasn’t been exactly the celebration year, so let us all savour every little chance it gives us to dress our best and what better than Diwali! 
In light of this here’s dropping another ‘not so chohti’ video of me getting ready for a Diwali party( Didn’t get to attend one this year sadly) 

Just putting it here for any kind of inspiration you want to take out of it. raw, pure and simple, didn’t put in too much effort in editing for following reasons: 

1. Time crunch: I intended to post this a week earlier but I was having a relaxed yet adventurous birthday week.

2. Intent to make it a appreciation post for mum’s killer styling instinct and gratitude for keeping us with or else my page would be super flop! 

3. To show how while it can seem very daunting to drape a saree it can elevate your fashion game several folds if styled right. 
//She used a simple black georgette saree and added in a little oomph factor using one of my sheer bra I got from Sarojini in 50bucks! //

4. Show you what a tedious, tiring job it is to shoot a video when you struggle with space (because your dog is everywhere), light, and your urge to constantly eat and dance around 😂

5. Lastly to give you loads of positive, happy Diwali feels!! ✨

P.s Tried to make it bearable with a choice of a good song. 

Cheers!

latestIgtvVideos.title: Celebrating the Onset of festive season with a Garba look!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Who else is missing the Garba nights this year? 

I have always loved festive season! And garba night is one the highlights of this season. 
I attended one of these couple of years back and being someone who loves dancing I thoroughly enjoyed it. 
Everbody dressed in bright extravagant outfits, loud music, the whole vibe is so colourful and happy! 

Hopefully all of this will be over soon, I will definitely attend one again next year until then Here’s a quick video of me dressed in one of my mum’s created version of Garba outfits (I felt like I was in class 2 when she use to dress me up for my dance competition) 

The blouse/crop top is from @bibaindia which I think with its perfect with its pompom sleeves, teamed it with a mustard colour skirt. 

P.s I am not very good at dandiya moves but I tried to copy some of the steps from my favourite garba song. I hope you enjoy the video! ✌🏻

And again, Happy Navratri everyone! 🌞

latestIgtvVideos.title: 3 quick summer date looks!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I intended to make this a more furbished video, but I am super lazy when it comes to editing a video. 
So here’s a quick fun compilation of videos we created!
What you will see in this video apart to ‘How to dress this summer in 3 quick ways!’ (Not that you can go out anytime soon but there’s hope). - what I do these weekends.
- what too much isolation looks like.
- struggle to keep my hair together.
- how to keep your dog away from biting your ass.
- how my mum is an expert at filming my videos.
- what a mess I create while shooting.
- a lot of underarm hair (because why bother shaving 😂)
- what an amazing dancer I am 💃🏼 .
But hey you got to do something to keep yourself sane! 😬
